But it is a good choice for the night before take an early flight.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jesse Medlong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVsJ0X9buOrLtMdNh3VVgfgGD08ZPxyTDeor9mjIYMuv0aWJd9l=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I enjoyed my stay at the hotel.
For international guests, you will need to present your passport upon checking in. They will make a photo copy of it.

They cleaned up the room every day for us. Be aware that you need to turn a switch on for the hot water. You must use your room key or the paper tag on the complimentary water and place it in the slot next to the light switches to turn everything on in the room.

The continental breakfast is from 7am - 10am. Breakfast is the same thing every morning. You can order a breakfast to go in the morning (it's just a sandwich and bottled water).

You may leave your room key at the front desk for the day if you would like. You may have to have the room key reprogrammed throughout your stay if you're there for a while.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"zillusia100","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcqjfyADTZteN6UQjkfmI_GEkLkHcE0ELlx5mF7J8mlJ0xtKNb2Z0W14ZGUWvDdJggyxw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"My 1st my impression of this hotel was good. So I recommended my friends to check in as well. But the hotel continues to disappoint a 2nd consecutive time. How can this hotel allow overbooking of rooms and expect affected guest to compromise either to a lower quality hotel or to expect us to just combine our rooms? If the basic honoring of guest's booking can so easily be comprised, how can we ever trust this hotel again? To make things worse, we even went down personally to the hotel a few days before our check in date to ensure the hotel has our booking correctly received due to the prior similar incident happened in December 2018 when the hotel also says no room for us after we booked the rooms. The hotel staff was friendly & accommodating. The food was nice & acceptable. The room was clean, spacious and the atmosphere around gave me comfortable. I truly enjoyed during my stay in this hotel. The location is most suitable for the locals who are travelling frequently by a highway bus as it is located very close to the highway bus terminal. I highly recommend the Holly Hotel for locals and foreigners as well who are looking for a hotel in this area in Yangon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lindsay Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdVsxDWqDDLG62Q3M3dmLlHORJs5jz0NWRJO3cP21KtRNPfosO7RpofjnbUgpyNjOTDew=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I loved Holly Hotel! Here are the reasons why:||First off, after a long day bus from Bagan, Holly Hotel was just a hop and a skip away from the Aung Mingalar Highway Bus Station (about 500m-1200m depending on where your bus arrives - Aung Mingalar Highway Bus Station is just massive!). My bus stopped about a 1.2km walk from Holly Hotel, but I was able to walk there within 15 mins (I'm a fast walker, and I had only a small little backpack). The hotel is ideal for transit by bus, and is equally convenient for transit by air (located only about 6km from the airport). For me, Holly Hotel was perfect, since I arrived to Yangon from Bagan by bus, and was set to depart by airplane the next afternoon. The hotel negotiated a flat fare taxi for me to the airport for 10,000 kyat, so I could safely spend out my remaining currency without being caught off guard.||On that note, there is a large shopping mall located 1.4 km up the road. It's called "Terminal M," and it has many restaurants/food courts, major retailers and most importantly a massive supermarket in the basement called "Ocean Supermarket." I walked to the supermarket from the hotel in about 15 mins (again, I'm a fast walker). It's safe to do so, just be aware you will be walking on the highway, so walk and cross the road with vigilance! I was able to spend out my remaining currency here, with great selection and prices!||Re: location, there are no food options nearby the hotel, so best be prepared for that! Unless you walk up to Terminal M, or come prepared with food for dinner at the hotel like I had done, you will find yourself in short supply. There are 2 small convenience stores across the street with basic supplies like water, crackers, cookies, instant noodles and other packaged foods which I couldn‚Äôt make out. The one convenience store directly adjacent has a big selection of wine! I was very happy to find wine in such an industrial area, and happily bought a bottle for a relaxing evening! Prices were reasonable.||Upon arrival at the hotel, I was greeted warmly by reception staff and check-in was swift. This was appreciated, since I had had a long travel day from Bagan!||My room was quite large, and very comfortable! Basic furniture such as a desk, chair, two bedside tables, and ample luggage storage (a large wooden bench and also a large wooden cabinet) were available! Air conditioning was strong, wifi signal was terrific (probably the best I've had in all of Myanmar so far), and the room was a welcome relief from the humidity. The room also came with a mini fridge (stocked with mini bar items such as water, a selection of sodas, and instant noodles), an electric kettle, 4-in-1 coffee (LOL, that's a first! Not sure what the 4th ingredient is!?), 2 coffee mugs, water glasses, 2 bottles of water with compliments, and 2 spoons.||Bathroom amenities included: 2 dental kits, 2 shower caps, bar soap, in shower shampoo and shower gel dispensers, and 2 combs. Toilet paper was in short supply, but staff were able to supply more when asked!||Shower and tap water were hot (perfect temperature) and water pressure was strong! Toilets were spotless!||Beds were super comfortable. Linens felt brand new and super clean. Pillows were the perfect firmness as was the mattress. Bedside lighting was also nice!||The room was equipped with flatscreen tv, with a few English channels to choose from - for one night, I was entertained enough! Sports channels namely, but there were also 2 movie channels in English as well.||The hotel has a cafe on the ground floor where breakfast is also served. It's called Holly Cafe! I didn't eat there, but prices looked reasonable. Breakfast buffet was fair, but not amazing, namely because I'm not one to enjoy Asian cuisine at breakfast (fried rice, noodles and greasy vegetables). I made do with what was on offer, as there were fried eggs, saut√©ed chicken breast with vegetables, fresh cut vegetables and fresh cut fruits available. Myanmar hotels mostly cater to Asian tastes, so one must be a bit flexible when traveling in this region! My only complaint would be the lack of availability of plain, no sugar added coffee/Nescaf√© (only 4-in-1 coffee packets were available), but I make it a point to carry my own in this region so I wasn't without.||Staff kindly allowed me to check-out an hour later, giving my time to regroup! They also helped me to remove the SIM card from my phone since I couldn't locate a paper clip or pin. Staff were extremely kind and helpful! ||Overall I enjoyed my stay at Holly Hotel! It was perfect for my transit needs, and allowed me a comfortable space to regroup, repack, and get organized for my next leg of travel! Excellent price to suit my budget also! But I also didn‚Äôt find accommodation in all of Myanmar to be terribly expensive either!||Thank you to all the staff for your kindness and hospitality! I loved Myanmar and will absolutely be back in the future!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Saothiha Htut","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV8KqBQ2mSbIhcBEccSxcNJqSW9tNc9EdjCEWtVKx5Vkk4wotFH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"üëç Nice room, very tidy room and also in

I just stayed one night for a next day flight and I'd highly recommend for that purpose. Only thing that left a bad taste ..was that they gouged me on the taxi to the bus station .  from airport to KC was 5000. approximately same distance and time KC set price at 15000 kyat which is dishonest.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Theo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1q9-gRFTa-cXzjc58mcRbRj__l9RydXLgOSW0ZmxRcQ0xXuRm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I loved my stay here. It felt like I had my home office again. The hotel does not look like much from the outside but when you come in it is like a MUSEUM! So many contemporary art pieces.

I enjoyed my stay here a lot. The facilities and amenities were well kept, I would argue this was the fanciest hotel I have been to in Myanmar by price. The amenities feel like it is at least 3.5 star, but this hotel is actually just a 2 star.

Electricity is always on 24/7 and the internet is pretty decent. I had zoom calls without much lag!

One downside though is every service here is EXPENSIVE. Laundry, food, breakfast are all above average priced. The only saving grace is that they give you free airport transfers. But I guess that is their business model, cheap brief layover stays.

Also, they tried to keep my passport safe for me in a folder. I didn't appreciate that at all, they should have brought me my passport back as soon as they didn't need it! I had to ask for it back...

Finally, the location (aside from being close to the airport) is horrible. Only 2 restaurants are nearby and they are both average at best, with one being better because if pricing. No convinient stores at all, you can't buy snacks or any thing else you need like shampoo without taking a taxi to the middle of the city.

Overall it was a good stay, I would comeback again a day before my next flight out of Myanmar. Other than that, you won't find me here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPpRoJwxxqXNEDXcgrqo_eMbOUO0IZhJ6Bety0F&fid=0x0:0x2ff287e0257c17c6"],"When":"2024-1-16"},{"Name":"Ibnu Wardana","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbrXgBCrE6NsGI33Zeb4XabLnpNHQJxaclDdhzJB8p-UWuGR26=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Located several hundred meters from the Yangon International Airport. title: Diamond Star Hotel
address: No. 84/85, Thudamar Road, 2 Ward, North Okkalapa Tsp
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Nel F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeNj0UTN0yIrCGyJ0JhWwDODOg5QjAH0gdfB9Ji-oFl0zWFI-YVmhNAr-FGLycdpIjFmw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Rooms in this budget hotel are tiny, with enough room to fit only a bed and smallish bathroom, with a few very modest furnishings, small TV screen and thankfully very functional AC. title: Seasons of Yangon International Airport Hotel
address: W42P+3G5 Seasons of Yangon International Airport Hotel, Airport Estate, Mingaladon Township, Yangon
descriptions: Simple rooms in a low-key airport hotel with a restaurant, an outdoor pool & a free airport shuttle.
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Stm I","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"OK, so it is not the newest or most luxurious property, but it fully met our needs and expectations.  We stayed in a deluxe double room, which was exceptionally large and comfortable and clean.  The bed was comfortable.  The aircon was quiet and worked well.  The bathroom was very clean and spotless (no mould).||||On arrival, we walked across from the international terminal (about five minutes: across the road outside the terminal, through a break in the fence to access the car park, then through the right hand side car park (bus park) then across another road to the hotel).  We were given a free transfer to the domestic terminal early the next morning.  We let them know on check in that we were checking out early, so they had a light breakfast pack awaiting for us on check out in lieu of breakfast in the restaurant.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mark A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I spent a night here in between flights with my 14 yo son. The Hotel is very tired and in need of a make over. The rooms are very basic but clean. The bathroom was old but the water was hot. Just remember to turn on the red hot water button near the room door to heat the water up first. It took me a couple of hours to sus this out. The TV has very basic channels, and if you don't like soccer, there is not much else in English. I didn't try the \"Chinese\" restaurant, and wouldn't recommend it. The pool looks like a health problem if you had the courage to get in! The location is clos to both terminals, and took me about 10 min to walk through the car park to reach the hotel. Take you luggage trolley with you. The beds were small, but comfortable, and the A/C looked new and worked well. If you only have a short time between flights, then this place would suit. If you can be bothered taking the hour or so to get into town, then its probably worth looking elsewhere.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"zo khai thawng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXE9un7ZbeYAhuLShcM6W_FMd51dNrzzwcUczL1YfEPH58anN5Q5w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"If you don't smoke ,you can't stay that place\nAll ok ,but suitable for smoking person only","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Hrusikesh Patra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwhcKMlMAYJiiG4wGMbZ2znegt6w5bjjjwUCWhX_MMb8XG6gXk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Stayed here for a night in December-2017. Good for a transit stay otherwise there are good options inside the city.\nThe hotel is close to the airport and is about 5 minutes of walk away. Hotel looks good from outside but rooms are old.  We reached in the evening and had a morning flight to catch, hence worked out well for us. I would not recommend this hotel for more than 1 night. There is a food complex right in front of this hotel and we had a good dinner there.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jim L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This is my fifth stay and things continue to improve slowly. Breakfast is still quite poor but you can order omelette or other eggs. They do not tell you this and they have very little English. It is only 2 minute drive or 5 minute walk to the airport. Free transfer offered. Probably would only stay here because so close to airport and the traffic in Yangon is very bad. There prices have come down due to increased competition. This time I paid $60. title: Grand Garden
address: No.8 Airport Street, Yangon
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"myint Htun ko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJBhjRKOqxuLrdKYWWvO6uORWWqbBR_E0_P4H82iDw_kesBiQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The location is remote and hard to find. The receptionist is blind. You'll have to carry your own suitcase. Call 12 hours in advance to book a room, show up with no record of the reservation. A one-day stay requires advance payment, which is more expensive than telephone inquiry. The elevator did not reach the highest level, the most irritating is the sound insulation effect is very poor, the door noise of other rooms, the phone call noise, the elevator lifting noise, etc., almost did not let you sleep. The garbage in the hotel room needs to be taken to the outside trash can. Isn't room service what a hotel is all about?","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tamara C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We spent one night at Grand Garden Hotel Yangon as a layover between a flight from Inle Lake and one to Jaipur via Bangkok. As others have said, this hotel is very close (5 minutes) from the Yangon airport and very convenient for an overnight stay pre-flight. The pick up and drop off were prompt and all we could hope for. I booked a standard room, and we were first put in a 3rd floor (top floor) room. This room would have been unbearable. These top rooms sit under a slanted roof that appeared to be uninsulated since we could see light shining through in places. This meant that the ceiling of the room (the roof) was one large radiant heater. The finish-out in the room and bathroom was less than expected as well. When I called downstairs to say the heat was unbearable, they quickly moved us to an upgraded 2nd floor room that was perfectly cool and much more nicely finished out, so all was good. Food was good if not remarkable. The pool was dingy looking, so we passed on that. There is a fitness center in a building across the parking lot, but it was very warm inside. We walked the street outside the compound: Some interesting bits, but definitely a suburban slum and no sidewalks. My 4-star rating would probably be a 3.5, but the location and free shuttle service are excellent for airport access and the upgraded room was very nice. So, if like us, all you need is a clean, convenient and well-priced overnight stay near the airport, Grand Garden Hotel Yangon is the ticket. Staff is friendly and helpful as well.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joao Carlos V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Besides having communicated the hotel our arriving time, flights, etc... They never sent someone to pick us up.|No apologies were offered.|The hotel is nice, clean, confortable beds, large rooms, tv, minibar, porter service, lift...|We were given the wrong bed configuration at first, then we were moved, but it ended up being a smaller room. Since we were only there for the night, we didn't bother in complaining.|At 3am we needed to leave to the airport, and it was very hard to wake the receptionist up. He called us the transfer and went straight back to sleep.|","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Andy Moughtin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKJcsUB6yttRBkpYAduYRKBMRN887AyNcIXhbtwXEJ1Fg0sH3IW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Only spent a night here. Hotel seemed great. Room very comfy with lots of thoughtful touches. Staff very friendly and helpful. One down side was that the lift doesn't go to the third floor (could be an issue for some) and the rain was so noisy on the roof. Floors 1 and 2 wouldn't have this I'm sure.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Emilia Taylor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJGB2yQDyIcbSK2hsJbAE9abhwtxurcMu9ReWa82CZwgxxYstk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I stayed in this hotel for two days. The room I had was very clean especially the bathroom. Location of the hotel is near the airport and if you want to go to the city just called the taxi to the airport and then you go by bus cause the price high by taxi.The breakfast in the hotel is average but your stomage will full. Unfortunately while there is swimming pool in this hotel but we can't swim because of the renovation of the pool.,didn't know until when. Cause Yangon is very hot and dusty this hotel is like hidden gem. And as I lover cat üêà I was surprised that in this hotel I saw the cute cat in front of the hotel! What a lovely hotel!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Seung-won Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJXU2hasb5KMwlpVJIEoMIaSSwPIwVA8cdf1uPPQ5GdoFw8-A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It is a good transit hotel near Yangon International Airport with moderate room rate, if you do not expect a cozy place for relaxation with tranquility and long stay.

The hotel suggests free airport pickup and sending that would take less than 8 minutes. For airport pickup, call the reception and wait 10 minutes at designated place. In a while you can find a hotel staff strolling around holding a sheet of paper printed hotel name on.

They will suggest you a breakfast box if you have to leave too early to have hotel breakfast: simple sandwich, a boiled egg, and a bottle of water.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jo B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This hotel is very reasonable for the price. The staff are very helpful and very friendly especially if you‚Äôre travelling on your own as I was. The room was clean and looked nice. It was a little noisy by the road and and the blinds didn‚Äôt really keep the light out. Apart from those minor issues it was a good stay and very good service","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"kian wee chau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVc4qC3YFjs7c-ek9IZoWDoPgw4w6OoEt6GFySRD1pmiW4DyifM9w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I stayed in this hotel one night.
Pro:
1) The room is very bright.
2) Pillow has different softness.
3) The room is new.
4) The receptionists are friendly.
5) It provides free airport drop off / pickup.
6) It provides massage services. MMK 8,000 per hour. Hotel guest has 25% discount which is MMK 6,000.
7) WiFi signal is good and fast.
8) Dinner at restaurant was delicious for what I ordered. There were Steamed fish, Tom yum soup and black pepper prawn.
Con:
1) The swimming pool area is lack of regular cleaning. The concrete floor next to the pool has obvious dirty stain.
2) The window curtains can't block the day light. When sun rises, I can feel the day light already. My sleep was disturbed. 2 pictures were taken without turning on any light in the room.
3) The balcony door doesn't have any curtains at all. This is another source of day light that disturbing my sleep.
4) Many mosquito were in the restaurant.
5) Buffet breakfast offered simple choices. Local food, bread, porridge, typical Indian food, fruits.
6) Varieties of TV programs are limited. Only few are English. Signal was not good too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPamBSjoI0PwMKEXt4W9c2yruVdrGkUGIYdg6f7&fid=0x0:0x43a270e8c9d016f8"],"When":"2019-10-4"}]

for a Overseas Community Service Trip with 20 others from my school. ||Location of hotel is quite near the airport by van, bus schedules are impossible to understand as a foreigner. ||Hotel was 7 stories high with no lift. Had to lug a 20kg suitcase up 7 floors as I happened to be on the highest floor haha. But staff were really friendly and would help you carry up if they see you struggling!||Hotel room was really really spartan. Very old TV set that we didn't use. Our room has a king sized bed for 2 and 3 mattresses on the floor. A very narrow walkway in the room, so barely any space to open your suitcase or walk. ||Toilet and bathtub was quite dirty and stained, but very good by Myanmar standards so I would not complain. Water pressure was poor and took 20 minutes to shower on average. Aircon was cold but quite noisy, and the street traffic at all hours made it quite hard to sleep. Lots of insects and mosquitoes throughout the building. ||Free wifi in the small lobby, and breakfast was really tasty. There is a 24 hour restaurant just to the right of the hotel with really good food though. ||The staff were really really friendly, and made the stay overall rather pleasant though.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Peter P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qd0Gzx7-o-W0qn7F-oHhorx-ann6UFYRniBmE7Ar1MhRFtO-x6vY7U2LNCPC1lcQidkpw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This is a very simple small hotel located in Mingaladon province, quite far from Yangon and not very suitable if you want to go to Yangon very often. It is close to Yangon International Airport, however you must take a taxi (experience in itself) to get there. There is a dirty and busy street in front of the hotel, with buses operating, but for a foreigner the system of the buses is almost ununderstandable. Alternatively you can use Yangon Circular Railway, a great attraction in itself, which can bring you to the Yangon main station in about one hour (the train rides very slowly, but shows you the real life of Myanmar). Wai Bar Gi station is within walking distance from the hotel (about 20 mins), however be prepared to walk through a very poor neighborhood and on soil roads. Aung Mingalar Bus Terminal is about 600 m from the hotel. The hotel itself has very simple rooms (just bed, table with chairs, small TV set and a very simple bathroom), any view was destroyed during my visit by a construction. The road is very noisy, so it is better to keep windows closed, there is quite loud air-conditioning. The \"bathroom\" is just another empty room with shower and toilet, no frills, and during my stay there was no hot water in my room (maybe they could have probably fixed it if I would tell them, but it was OK in those hot and humid days). Bed is OK, linen is provided. There is a free wi-fi, but working only downstairs in a small lobby. Simple breakfast is included in the price. There are several small shops around, where you can buy water and something to eat, however do not put hygiene under a microscope... The whole neighborhood is very poor, but that is simply Myanmar. But the people are very nice and some of them in the hotel try to speak some words in English, however they are not used to foreign visitors very much. If you are looking for a very cheap accommodation not far from the airport (which was my intention), this hotel can serve you, but be prepared for a very spartan conditions. I didnt expect too much, hence the average mark I gave it.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Aung Thura","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKYtFxJaEuhyT0CdqObyoXJPafgNk6NGnzrJtw53OfGssD8rg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"bad rooms and furnitures, foods are in maximum prices...rooms need to maintain... tatal all...rating 0star.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"PhyoThu Naing","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWID3ECFCghWgaGj1tECjvGDtvLpqnS3n-QKKduZ4q9ZP5i8P41=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Fair price.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jack Whaley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNw5COnu2ArPITmKyEygJceUJDFToWwbx0x_zLo5ZRre8s6Hw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The rooms are at a very low quality for how much you pay. Bed bugs are present","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"AB DF","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLw80jr14sfGdoNHoqHGpQvriVPHJ8zeNLeC70kibLUTv6FfQM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Poor standard of commodities. On the good side, the room was clean and the bed was comfortable. It is in a suburb next to Million Coins Restaurant. Across the street is a new soccer stadium. Otherwise, the neighborhood seemed safe but 'iffy.' Lots of poverty most everywhere in this country. A limited breakfast is included with the room price. There are four choices all of which include juice and powdered coffee.||||Questionable was the top floor where they did the laundry. I think there were two electric washers, but one lady was scrubbing towels on the roof floor. Another lady was ironing sheets. Washing was hung out in the air to dry. Standard stock in the bathrooms were packaged condoms, restocked when rooms were cleaned. Bathroom had a shower that soaked the entire bathroom floor since the small drain hole must have been too tiny. This is possibly similar to any third-world hotel which costs $28 per night.||||Worst was our confirmed reservation. We arrived at 1:00 am from a delayed flight. None of the three young men at the desk could speak English. Fortunately, our driver could speak Burmese. He told us that there were no rooms - sort of. Certainly they would not give us one. Possibly with condoms in the rooms caused our being sent away . . . who knows? We were given no help to find accommodations. Our driver (head of a school where we were teaching) allowed us to crash on a mat in his school office. Although a bit arrogant for me to say, no-one could speak English though the manager could somewhat communicate to us. ||||Depending on your expectations, it did not meet mine. Thus, I would not recommend it. Rooms and bed sheets are dirty and old. WiFi is too bad. TV is older than me and only 6 channel lines. This hotel have absolutely guest house standard.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tyler S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"My family and I visited Yangon in October and stayed for almost 2 weeks at the Royal Golden View hotel in North Dagon. The staff did everything they could to make us feel very comfortable and welcome in their hotel. The restaurant served a variety of food for the included breakfast buffet. There was also an available lunch or dinner menu which was reasonable in price and the food was fairly good as well.  The room accommodations were reasonable and very similar to other hotels we have stayed at in the area. We did wind up moving rooms towards the end of our stay into a larger suite. This made our stay much more comfortable at the end. The location of the hotel is very easily accessible from the airport and to the north and east side of the city.The new Myanmar Plaza is only about 15 minutes taxi ride and was very convenient for shopping, additional dining, and to pick up bottled water or other sundries as needed. The staff did a very good job of helping us manage taxi rides and directions and were very helpful with their ability to speak English as well. During our stay there Internet connection was not available and did produce some challenges for us. There seems to be something lost in translation as to why the Internet was not working but it appeared that maybe because it was the slow season they had disconnected the Internet because of the cost and the low number of visitors during our stay. Overall, we had a very reasonable stay and always looked forward to getting back to the hotel at the end of the day after we had been out and about. Despite some of the challenges with the Internet, the staff was very helpful and we may consider staying there again.  You would not go wrong if this were a short stop over or overnight stay while connecting through at the airport. The prices were very reasonable and the accommodations were comfortable.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Magdalene L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I have stayed here for the past 4 years annually.  Never fail to come back to this hotel - its about half hour from the city (with no traffic jam) otherwise longer.  ||||This hotel has nice surroundings with good friendly staff and a chance-upon experience to meet the friendly bosses of this hotel this year. The room is clean and breakfast is decent.  During this trip, I noticed that there is a drop in standard in terms of breakfast food.  The noodles ware not replenished on time and the coffee is very diluted. A coffee machine would help to solve this problem. The coffee-house has lots of mosquitoes if you dine in the evening. However, the staff were friendly and helpful too.  There is also a mini gym available beside the coffee house.||||Rooms are of decent size too and they are clean too.||They have improved in their WIFI as well but still unstable as the infrastucture in this country is not that good but the hotel tried to give their best in this area.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"C073","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeYuXGoFc9HnT35lAJ46cKDIsHY7nNIKUKz_f8yINNlqyrU48jCx-4ctPzihRKgde030w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"There is not really a reason to stay close to the airport in Yangon because access to it from downtown is still quite swift and easy most of the time. However, for someone looking for accommodation in the vicinity of the airport, the Golden View Hotel may be an acceptable choice for a short layover IF they do not want to go to the city. The hotel is quite new and the premises clean. Rooms are small but comfortable with air-con, flat-screen TV, minibar and safe. The bathrooms are simple but nice and there is a full set of amenities on offer. Wifi is free and offers acceptable coverage - at least in the Myanmar context of perennially slow and unstable internet connections. The staff is very friendly and helpful. The hotel has a restaurant on its premises. The selection of food and beverage will cover basic needs for a short-term stay. The hotel is situated on the banks of Ngammoeyeik Creek, a tidal tributary to Yangon River in otherwise rather poor-looking surroundings. Unless you intend to rough it out, eating places that will fit the average tourist's basic needs are rare around the hotel. There is a bakery shop with cafe at the beginning of U Wisara Road (some 2.5km away). It is very popular among locals and serves decent food for a snack. For a proper meal you may want to move closer to town. Getting a taxi is not difficult at any time because for some reason there are plenty of taxis driving along U Wisara Road. Apart from the remote location (in relation to downtown Yangon), the other drawback of this hotel were that noise travelled easily along its corridors and through the light doors. If your stay coincides with that of a Korean or Chinese travel group, chances are that light sleepers will have to wake up at the same time. During the time of our stay, there was work being done in the environs of the hotel adding further to the noise level. ||Breakfast was included and included a standard selection of fruit, eggs, toast, cake, fruit punch (called ‚Äújuice‚Äù), congee and some warm dishes etc. ||In conclusion: Similar to Sri Lanka after the end of the civil war, Myanmar‚Äôs hospitality industry went off the rails when it benefited from a sudden swelling of tourist arrivals after the opening of the country some three years ago. Prices for accommodation have more than doubled. They may not be exorbitantly high but I like to compare all deals with what you get in Thailand because it is the place where you get the best value-for-money if you look for it and most people can relate to this popular destination. Everything I have come across this trip, cannot remotely compare with what you get in Thailand for the same price.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chuck Huckaby","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVpbWZRZuxWnvS4180mBywsGxRjQ1la5FKeg3UQGuRJcFIq8GUNxg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Just a short ride from the new Yangon International Airport, the Royal Golden View is a fine hotel with free breakfast. We stayed in one of the bungalows and enjoyed the accommodations!

An excellent price and excellent staff as well!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZATgFg001xbo3vbkiny90L6MF1rujEZoFlEEV&fid=0x0:0xc729d88ec47294e2"],"When":"2018-9-9"},{"Name":"David H√∏gh Christensen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL4peoh9ZS2NbpLauGBtPGGcp_VJrES_LkfScARjVUJs1VJ9w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Really nice place. It's a bit outside the city centre which makes It hard for taxis. At least we needed 3 attempts to go to the hotel.

It's clean and the staff is nice.

Has a good view over the river","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Maineiac24","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Stayed here twice in November 2014.  As Yangon hotels goes it's pretty good for the price. You can spend a lot more and get the same thing. Myanmar has only been "open" for a few years and so they still do some annoying things the "closed" way, however, it is getting better. But if you are expecting something like you would get in BKK or HKG or SIN then you'll be disappointed. However, all in all, this is the best for the price I've stayed at in YNG in my history there going back 9 years.||||Good Points||1. Clean. Rooms and hallways are clean and well lit.||2. Staff is friendly, however, is hampered by the rules laid down by someone who is not on the premises. The staff has no authority to do anything on their own.||3. GREAT hot water showers. Each room has its own HW heater. Good volume, clean water, well heated.||4. GREAT bathrooms. New, clean. It is a "wet" bathroom but it is so much better than anything you are likely to get anywhere else outside of YNG. Getting back to this shower after a week elsewhere was the highlight of my trip.||5. Good Price. I paid $65 USD Cash for double occupancy. You must have cash and it must be cash that is in good shape. No marks. No tears. No dirt. They will simply refuse to accept anything that is not 95% perfect, so carry clean bills.||6. Fridge in the room. Good size TV. Air conditioning. Decent bed. Good sheets. Clean sheets. Great pillows. Good lighting in the room. Recessed LED ceiling lights. Well lit.||||Before I get to the Not So Good points. I did not eat at the hotel. I did not order any food there. I did not go to the restaurant. ||||Not So Good:||1. The AC in the rooms is VERY diverse depending on what room you get. We rejected 2 or 3 rooms before settling on one where the AC worked well. They will tell you, "wait 20 minutes and it will get cool".  So wait and se what happens.||2. The southwest facing rooms (front) are into the sun most of the day. The inside of the windows are so hot you can't touch them. The second floor is worse. The heat coming into the room from the balcony door, or window or even through the wall is amazing. It will make these rooms 20 degrees hotter then the other side of the hotel. If you have to have a SW facing room take the ground floor as the trees outside provide a bit of shade. However, the lobby noise may get to you.||3. Noisy. There are signs up all over the hallways asking people to be quiet. The walls are not insulated and are all cement or tile and it echoes around the place. Wear earplugs to bed.||4. Cash. You must have USD cash and it must be clean. If you say, "This is all I have." They still will not take a marked or barely worn or torn bill. The people at the desk are simply following orders and have no discretion in the matter. The boss will take it out of their pay if they take your bill.||5. Out of the way. The hotel is not near much of anything. Which is fine for me but may be bad if you are looking for shopping or restaurants.||6. English. Their English is fine if everything goes well, but if you have a problem or require something more than standard English they will struggle. However, they are very pleasant and look like they understand.||7. Internet is sketchy and slow and erratic.||||All in all it is the best for the price that I have found in Yangon so far. If you get a room where the AC works on the Northeast side, and you have been to the grocery store for your food, you can have a nice stay and get clean.","Images":null,"When":""}]

It was old hotel but relatively clean and well air-conditioned. Myanmar traditional noodle soup was unique and delicious with little salty taste. For one night stay, it was not bad but somewhat expensive (50 US dollar /day for double bed).","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Zenheart","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qcacbd8SUzOZ5BFqcuH0dUXFfPFzIfRWlhBQfTV3kcVPU69oUP_k10j49o8svvEcoldiA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"If you enjoy traveling back in time, then this is the hotel to stay to experience the days of old!! The large building is quite unique with many rooms within. The building is spartan and decent within. The rooms are clean but spartan. Although there is air conditioning, be prepared for a noisy night of air con noise from the old units. The toilet is big but very rudimentary. Expect power failures and the flush not working. However, if you have basic plumbing skills, that could easily be fixed rather than calling on the reception. You may have a language barrier!! Beds and toilets are really retro, so are the light fixtures. There is a small TV set with many channels. If you enjoy old Korean dramas dubbed in the local vernacular, then it's will be entertainment!! Oh yes, no towels or soap is provided. Bring your own towels, toiletries, and yes your own toilet paper. Also, no drinking water is provided. If you need any of these, these have to be paid for I guess. Breakfast is very rustic with a piece of plain bread with a fired egg. Coffee comes in a 3-1 satchet. So bring your own food to supplement!! There is supposed to be wifi in a small corner of the lobby. But don't count on that. There is never a connection when I was there. So you will really enjoy the real world without the lure of the internet!! The surrounding buildings are a sight to behold!! It's a walk back to the past with very old buildings. Enjoy the local culture and the endless heavy traffic as you try to cross the 6 lanes road!! No pedestrian crossing unfortunately. Make sure you buy travel insurance before you attempt to cross the road!! There are small Internet caf√©s nearby and a new but small shopping mall. To enter the mall, you have to pass through a metal detector gate!! There is a small but nice cafe within walking distance which sells decent food!! We were fortunate to have our local friends to do the communication for us.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Zwe Khant","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJZpZrJjR5at3GEzKcu5raisVCO8n2ybcTFm9UiPJMbGvvsfQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lay Naing","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJWE2BtceOGfK84nFm8oGtnOCcSPd9D9nc9LFrgSHhFQgZE6g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Htet Wai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWx-ThnP79KaO4YTSZfWYYfO24OCi1WO7npUzAmlTzV3QGXS3Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"·Ä°·Äõ·Äô·Ä∫·Ä∏·Ä°·ÄÜ·ÄÑ·Ä∫·Äï·Äº·Ä±","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"T. It has a TV, mini bar and kettle which are all very useful! |It has a nice big bath room and super hot shower. |What made our stay particularly special were the staff all the maids and porters have been very smiley & friendly. I'm very grateful to the owner who went out of his way to help us with where to go while in Yangon & also where to continue our trip. |The lady at breakfast was lovely too, we had toast and fruit for the first couple of days but I'd recommend trying the Burmese coconut chicken noodle soup very tasty! |The location is out of the main city it's quite peaceful and it is in walking distance to the lake, it's also continent for the airport.|There are lots of nice places to eat nearby too. |It's excellent value for money, I'd definitely return! |Thanks very much :)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Georgiana F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdHDxxyBDO6igPA51sqxYAI1TTeuGvapT1sWSCJfPSgzOZltNlMhWmUDpj2A3v7zAw89g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I lived here for five months, March-July. It's a charming place with staff that go out if their way to be helpful. Breakfast is included. Mary will accommodate you as best she can with your breakfast preferences. I often order the fried vermicelli for dinner which the staff will bring to your room. The lodge is away from traffic and quiet with lots of greenery about. It's not a touristy place. You can't walk out the door to go shopping. But taxis are readily available to take you wherever you want to go. The front desk will help you with this. There is rudimentary laundry service. No dry cleaning. The air conditioning is wonderful. There are normal complimentary items like coffee, tea, bottled water, shampoo, soap, toothbrush. The lodge is past its glory days, but it's still got lots off charm to offer. The staff is a large part of that charm.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Anthony S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This hotel has surpassed my expectation massively. The room is extremely clean, the air conditioning is not at all loud and very efficient. The bathroom is brilliant, and instant hot water!||The tv has about 6 English channels which is more than enough, the minibar is well stacked and well priced.||The laundry service is fast and very reasonably priced, and the breakfast is great, good omlettes and fresh fruit!||And on top of that the staff are amazing, they will happily book a taxi for you and get cheaper non-tourist rates, also the owner gave us a lot of help deciding what to do here going above and beyond what we expected, which has really pleased us and made our stay that extra bit more pleasant and personal.||The staff are very attentive too, and try to make your stay as comfy as possible.||Great place, for an awesome price, very quite, and out of the city so no traffic noise and lots of wildlife to keep you entertained outside.||The ONLY complaint bieng extremely picky besides the occasional powercut is in heavy rain the metal roof makes a bit of a racket. Didn't bother me at all but light sleepers might want a different room in monsoon season.||How this isn't higher rates is absolutely beyond me!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kate W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdCjMUwIiBikRhCLHgN_0vyGAo1GvT8DEukiKQb1ujC_eFsFjYrQ0OvLoSxPtqmCdgvFA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I chose Highland Lodge for the affordable price and proximity to the airport for a one-night stay before an onward flight.  I was very pleasantly surprised by the friendly family feel and quiet, leafy setting.  ||||My request for an airport pick up was dealt with quickly and for a very reasonable price.  All of the staff spoke basic English and a couple were fluent - and very patient with my useless attempts to speak Burmese!  A simple but good breakfast featured fresh fruit and eggs. ||||The rooms were simple with beautiful hardwood floors looking out over a leafy courtyard.  The bathroom decoration was slightly dated but all in perfect working order and instant hot water.  Everything was spotlessly clean.  The wifi in Myanmar has a reputation for being a bit on-off but I found better reception across the country than I have at home in rural England.  ||||Highland Lodge is a bit of a trek to downtown Yangon so I would probably stay closer to town for a longer stay, but they provided a lovely welcome for my first night in Myanmar and a million times better than your usual impersonal airport hotel.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Myo Thant","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJuko0pnrYJwLLprNZvzxion3_Xftwkk8bk69_5QIKtTT5VWg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It is great.

Buses are also available","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Eve Baker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9xOV1ddwicNg0fxmU09hgyY3I2SNB34v8QnhdjaeKOHr-nQjH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I cannot rate this place highly enough. title: Hotel 9 Mile
address: V4JP+CRV Hotel 9 Mile, Tsp, No. 3/A (10/12/14), Taw Win, 1 Street, Yangon
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Michael B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This hotel is modestly priced ($50 double/twin, $60 double/twin with balcony, including breakfast) yet has exceptionally high standards. Just one year old (Oct 2015) it is in pristine condition and kept spotless throughout. Air conditioned bedrooms are spacious and have all you need. The beds are extremely comfortable with duvets and white linen and fresh towels are provided daily. The bathroom has a walk-in shower and there is always plenty of hot water. Staff are delightful and extremely helpful and the manager Zayar is always eager to oblige. We asked for coffees in our room one day and he immediately sent up a kettle with sachets of coffee, creamer and sugar - all complimentary. Breakfast is included - either Korean (the hotel is Korean owned, hence the excellent management) or Anerican (eggs, toast, fruit, coffee).  The restaurant serves only Korean food at lunch and dinner, but there are plenty of other restaurants nearby.||The hotel is in a quiet location, and is a little challenging to find at first (ask for Nine Mile Road at Ocean Centre and turn off this road at the Corola Hotel). The hotel is only a few minutes drive from the airport and pickups can be arranged for just 5000 kyats (about $4) which saves you haggling with local taxi drivers. ||I had been staying at another nearby hotel which I have used for years but standards were declining so moved to Hotel 9 Mile on the recommendation of a local friend. I didn't regret the move at all. The hotel is incredible value!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Steven L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Stayed 12 days. My main complain is the WIFI. It goes on and off. Even as we were leaving, they were still fixing the WIFI by installing a complete new system. The room is reasonably furnished but nothing fancy. Room size is big. Window view is that of a shower stall. Bathroom is a perpetural flood every time you take a shower. Breakfast is either Korean or American. I love the Korean breakfast. There is a massage parlor on site. Tried it but didn't like. They tend to grind your muscle against your bone. I thought that was not very good for the body. Otherwise price is reasonable. It is very difficult to communicate with the girls at the counter. They do not understand much English. I kept asking them to stop opening the window when they clean the room in the morning because of the mosquito but they do not seem to understand what I said. The manager speaks excellent English and is very helpful. Taxi fare to down town or anywhere for that matter is always 5000. Foreigners are taken advantage of because local pay much less (\u003e2000). It seems that it also applied to drinks and food too. They charge one higher price for tourist and one lower price for the local.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"slim s","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeSe9ibNVY65MpgeQh70I370foM0-7tEPyVc9CIfSq5Ekli093sZJVPBoLD5d5qPK_2rw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This hotel is located 9 miles away from CBD and very near to airport. It is exactly located in the small lane,which is connected to main road. So basically you can rest peacefully and quietly. Overview of hotel is average as old furnitures and bedding are used. Rooms are decorated with simple tiles but the room i was given was quite spacious and great point was that small balcony was attached to my room. Small mini fridge as per normal and small safe box,which was not functioning unfortunately were provided. There was small little tv with 3 channels ridiculously. Breakfast were served with two varieties, American breakfast and Korean breakfast. I tried American and it was simple dish and nothing special. I noticed i was the only non-korean in the dinning room and whole hotel i guess. Hence, this hotel can be considered as Korean hotel. There is SPA within hotel compound and i would say that is the only plus for this hotel. You should try the SPA though but don't get ur expectation too high on its decorations. So, for my point of review, i would rate this hotel as follows:|Price: 2.5/5|Service: 4/5|Room : 2.5/5|Breakfast : 2/5|Location : 4/5 ( as closer to airport and shopping mall nearby)|SPA :3.5/5|Over all : 3/5","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Stuart K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The hotel is very new.  The room was very neat and tidy.  The manager spoke very good English and was able to change money for us at the same rate as the money changers in town.  He was very helpful and organised his own vehicle to take us to the airport when the taxi was late.  ||Breakfast was either Korean (spicy) or American (sausages, eggs, toast). ||The staff were very friendly and helpful.  They would sometimes forget to replace our towels when they cleaned the room but quickly got us new ones when we asked.||WiFi was spasmodic.  One day I watched a youtube clip, the next day couldn't get my emails to download.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rits K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfnSFWXMd1oJu73a6IhdtgibYcjse2HKQTHeghNQd9Cyw8DYQQJZDCyh-TD68ehXuY-FA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I was referred here by my tour guide who is friends with the manager.  The manager was there to greet me getting out of the car.  I was pretty impressed.  The hotel is only 5 min from the airport...10 min through traffic.  That's the beauty of the place being so close.||||I had dinner at the restaurant.  This hotel mainly caters to Koreans who come to Yangon for golf excursions.  The Korean food was amazing.  Even the kimchee was true, original Korean made.||||The bed, like all of Myanmar, is hard.  But, I got used to it as we stayed at 7 hotels throughout our travel from 3* to 5*.||||I went to the Spa and had an 75 min massage.  The girls are quite young.....16-19 year olds.  The massage is a Thai style massage where they would manipulate your back and go through all kinds of contortions.  The beds are laid out very close to each other so you could hear the next person beside you.  It was only 10,000 which is about $12.00 US.  Amazing.  No wonder it is a very popular place.||||The staff is very friendly, service oriented and on the ball.  I paid $45 US for the night and was a happy camper. Maybe my price was good because it was a referral. Would definitely return here if we ever come back to Myanmar.  All in all a very satisfying stay.  Simple and detail oriented.  Thank you Hotel 9 Mile.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Heidi M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdcKHisBXAOJmIugCgnKbcAscQkQI1t40WdQAMXk1g3ttzWj18FtKnHxNeSUm5OfHPMtQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Our guide suggested we end our Burmese vacation with massages at a spa near the airport before our departure flight, and it was the perfect way to end our vacation and adventure in Myanmar!  Don't be fooled by the modest appearance, the facility is clean and the staff are very friendly and accommodating.  Like many Asian massages, you are not required to undress, and no oils are used.  But be warned, this is no Swedish Massage!  You are in for a treat if you're looking for a deep tissue massage that incorporates pressure points and stretching.  My masseuse not only massaged my entire body for 90 minutes, but she walked on my back, used her arms, legs and feet to maximize the impact, and stretched my arms, legs, back and neck.  All this for $15USD...unheard of!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"THEREE OHHW","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXliPRdggWK4MBtVeoCPy2Y3MNWfcs1hrsDx9jx4MJ93AkcJj2k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Impressive hotel. It's Really clean with excellent Service. They look after you very well. Fully serviced every day. Cold air conditioner. Crispy clean sheets, Good shower and toilet. Bar Fridge. Hair dryer. Staff extremely helpful in every way.  I would've stayed longer but they were booked out. So convenient ... close to a variety of Nice restaurants and eating halls. Hair dressers and a big sort of Super-market, A bit like Kmart but with groceries fruit etc as well. 250 US dollars for about 7 days. I Highly recommend it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP3S7ycjNjfG6q1L_N1VQLcIc3st2Jz_6kICCIS\u0026fid=0x0:0xa18e3c135e08a7a1"],"When":"2018-2-4"},{"Name":"Marty W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This is a good quiet place to stay in the city, relatively close to the airport with good taxi service to other points in the city. located off the street, its a bit hard to find the first time. Rooms are clean, basic, and the hot water showers are great. Wi-Fi intermittent. Breakfast is included, basic American or Korean. On premises restaurant is Korean/Chinese.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Wai Yan Min Khant","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIs1pY9NKlkN9KPMB4P0N0kKcSTo-GEwdfNGYXheBvsCoh2Bf8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I would like to offer some constructive feedback for service improvement based on our recent stay at your hotel on 16-17. We chose your hotel after carefully comparing reviews and services from other options, but unfortunately, the experience fell short of our expectations and what the reviews suggested.

Firstly, we called ahead at noon to inquire about early check-in but were told it wasn‚Äôt possible. We understand that early check-in is subject to availability, but this was disappointing. We checked in at 2 p.m. as directed.

During the check-in process, the reception team did not thoroughly verify our booking details. They requested full payment upfront despite our prior payment of half the charges via Kpay. We had to remind them to recheck the information, which was frustrating and could have easily been avoided with better attention to detail.

Secondly, our room was not ready upon arrival, even though we had informed the reception in advance of our arrival time. When escorted to the room, the staff knocked before entering, which raised concerns about whether they were unsure if the room was properly assigned to us. Additionally, the key card provided didn‚Äôt work, leaving us waiting outside for an extended period. The staff eventually opened the room with a master key but left us with the malfunctioning card instead of replacing it with a functional one. This was not only inconvenient but also unprofessional.

The state of the room itself was also disappointing. The bed was not properly organized, and the decorative pillows and blanket shown in your promotional photos were haphazardly stored in the wardrobe rather than being arranged on the bed. This lack of attention to detail made us question whether the room had been properly cleaned after the last guest‚Äôs stay. The staff member assisting us also did not offer any information about the facilities, and their tone and demeanor were far from what one would expect from hospitality staff. We felt disrespected and unwelcome.

Lastly, communication between staff was noticeably poor. Upon leaving for dinner, we informed the reception about the faulty key card and handed it over for replacement. However, when we returned, the staff on duty seemed unaware of the situation and even questioned whether we had handed in the key at all. This clear lack of communication between shifts added to our dissatisfaction.

Overall,  the service we received was far from the standard we anticipated, and we hope these issues will be addressed for future guests.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Pearl Su","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKmPkagE-Z23PA_7GpkkzZQ94VuUT3WYlPp5b7EJRlt0Efunw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It is located inside of the alley. title: LOTTE HOTEL YANGON
address: 82 Sin Phyu Shin Avenue, Yangon 11091
descriptions: Refined hotel featuring indoor & outdoor pools, plus dining, a cocktail lounge & lake views.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Sandhya Tamang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-Z1P6Raag8kMSHKxzLpdF7qW-PtPUa5EbZx2dVHrDPCUBUqfemA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Location-wise, it is convenient for people coming directly from the airport.
The room itself was clean, though the carpets seemed a bit worn. The staff service was satisfactory but not exceptional for a 5-star hotel.
The hotel also offers both indoor and outdoor pools, catering to guests who prefer swimming in different settings.

DO NOT BUY THE CLUB LOUNGE UNLESS THEY BRING IMPROVEMENTS: The club lounge experience was shocking, as the food provided was insufficient, especially during tea n talk time. Tea N Talk includes 2 mini cakes and a mini plate of pizza (they call it pizza but its a tiny mini sushi hahaha)This is a significant area that needs attention. The club lounge is also not worth it because no one buys it and as a result, they come up with sushi looking pizza menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFg5HM9_qmdMpBs-YSrfnw_W32qKQrU4ROnDgI&fid=0x0:0x1ce0d39a47ca647c"],"When":"2025-2-16"},{"Name":"aung ko ko Win","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKSLsCXVULCVlKDvsIVUBinTNszcYRk6xB_IHPuznv_6kk2Hmc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently had the pleasure of enjoying tea time at the Lotte Hotel and it was quite the experience. The cake was absolutely excellent, with a rich, flavorful taste, and the plating was beautiful‚Äîdefinitely a treat for the eyes as well as the taste buds.

However, the Americano coffee left a bit to be desired. The taste was rather light, and I feel the coffee could have been stronger to match the high standard of the other offerings.

The venue itself is spacious and comfortable, providing a welcoming atmosphere for a relaxing break. The staff were very friendly and attentive, offering great service throughout.

Parking was convenient, and although the price is on the higher end, it‚Äôs expected for an international hotel. Overall, a lovely experience, though I would recommend improving the coffee.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO0v7TPbn1NyxNUsQ8DEVFMOqvRe5YGnf8HNa3H&fid=0x0:0x1ce0d39a47ca647c"],"When":"2025-2-11"},{"Name":"Dmitri M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qczn4VDfUM6-AtEt-6oaNazFa-i9Fy6kqPVfGIlPil6vJulEYyK8t930jZwOW4hD80mzw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Excellent hotel. The elegant setting, combined with impeccable service, made it a memorable evening of networking and relaxation.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"ZtablE","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIr9Si6eCfbvJM-2BX2J14RU1xOmKhuRdSj899cXUSkfwXKHmU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I spent 3 nights there and I appreciate what staffs treated me so well, beautiful hotel with good location, good foods which I almost gave 5 stars.

title: Mango Hill

user_reviews:

We were very lucky to stay at the Mango Hill boutique hotel.  The staff are so friendly and kind.  We were tired from our trip but they made us a lovely dinner and we also had a great early breakfast before they drove us to the airport the following morning.  The rooms were clean and quiet and comfortable.  The manager Mr Than Htaik Aung was really interesting to talk to and very kind to us.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWKqFuU3n8HBUxsT2di1hifP1LhODXbSvU_FzfNXZcu4uhqh60=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Location
Approximately 10 min of car ride from Yangon International Airport.

Accommodation
Room is clean and spacious with a king size bed and plenty of space for luggage.
There is a attached toilet.
Drinking bottled water is available and replenished frequently.
Quiet environment for a good night sleep.
Scenery is lacking though.

Service
Staffs are friendly, professional and helpful. Able to converse in English. They are very attentive to the needs of the guests.

Food
Tried the traditional Burmese food. Nicely prepared and presented. The food tasted good too.

Transportation
Private car hiring can made through the staffs.

Places of interest
Mingala Royal Lake (15 min)
Tooth Relic Pagoda (20 min)
Both are walking distance from Mango Hill.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Annabel O","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I love staying in the smaller, family owned hotels in a new country. Anyway to cut the talk short, watch what you eat and don't be a fool.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dinesh kumar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_GuDRTv1WgjN1nG59cJbQ5XBwhgOcvyBTy3ErbwqA6oUWZWG3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"New review 2019:

The hotel has been upgraded with the same excellent service as before. The rooms are clean and maintained well. They even have an ATM in the lobby. There is a 24hour CityMart (local supermarket) nearby. Since the hotel is on the main road, you can easily get Grab (like Uber car sharing service) and go around the city.

Do read my previous review below:

*****************************
Old review from 2017 below:

We stayed in the hotel for 3 nights in the Superior twin room and 2 nights in the Junior Suite B with Bathtub. As most of the reviews have already mentioned,  choose the rooms towards the back of the hotel (away from the road) and preferably to the right (facing east), these rooms have a better view and also you will get a glimpse of the rising sun. The hotel's buffet breakfast is great and each day they have a special local cuisine. This, in my opinion, would be a very safe way to try out the local dishes. The staff can speak English and are very friendly. The rooms are clean and we'll  maintained. The only problem is  that the doors do not appear to be sound proof and could be a problem if there are a lot of guests moving in-and-out of their rooms. TIP: There is a City Mart outlet straight down the road, about 15mins walk. There is a hospital nearby. There are some great food places in about 15mins walk.  (Note: photos are from the Junior Suite B room #403)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTRys335Gz8GYnI6YYBqGeugAo2Gk_wDNJK7Uv&fid=0x0:0x2c8d2472717556e6"],"When":"2018-1-7"},{"Name":"Sandy‚Äôs Shine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXd9XwYaXMx0VXxehGbmy_BXGG7o4D1R7qOLglJAXom2nLJ9IM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best technology in the leather industry","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ian Borja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUNLX_Fs9Bq4tJkkoiCk_V6a2wYuYVowqo_cuP2tYcQNCXRug1DBw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Small hotel of about 20 rooms. They do have good bed sheets, nice cozy room, very clean toilet and bathroom, and their towels are nice too.

They also have a simple buffet breakfast but would surely be filling. They have the normal fried rice, noodles, veggies, fishball, mominga, congee, bread, coffee & tea, different spreads, cereal, juice and fruits.

All staff, including the owner James, are very friendly  and they will make sure you will have the best stay.

Downside is location is in a main highway, but the noise is bearable. It is located a bit far from downtown area. Cab fare though is very inexpensive in Myanmar especially if you use Grab. If you let the front desk of the hotel book your Grab ride, you will even get a.discount.

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Sao Bran Aung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXns7Z0qbXUBvDEs378h_42ng4jdjelffQK1IRBjUzg22xU2B0Yyw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I recently stayed at Hotel Mindhama and would like to share my experience.

**Breakfast:** The breakfast provided is quite affordable and offers an average selection. It's a decent start to the day, but don't expect anything extraordinary.

**Room Condition:** One notable downside was the state of the blankets. They were not neat and tidy, which detracted from the overall comfort of the stay.

**Amenities:** On the positive side, the Wi-Fi was good, allowing for smooth and uninterrupted internet access, and the air conditioning worked excellently, ensuring a comfortable room temperature throughout my stay.

**Bathroom:** The bathroom facilities were just acceptable. While functional, they could benefit from some improvements to enhance the guest experience.

Overall, my stay at hotel Mindhama was mixed with some highlights and areas needing improvement. [{"Name":"LuLu Myat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9F7c2WM84icuQXNynYbQXGZ_GjZjqNaOzeA7ZAfKWHweccyr4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Room- If the room is in 4th floor , the bathroom water pressure and temperature will hard to adjust and mostly cold water will come.If unfortunate, the yellowish water will come out from the shower.
Service-Convenient payment method applies for all rooms.
Location-Hard to reach because it is located in the far end of the street .","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Latte Srei","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJsaA2ORkU4r-fTioqf6EWyFFL2WlPNxYoiAcn2hlUbe_LgiA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"This is our 2nd stay at Galaxy. The rooms are expensive. The restocking of supplies is poor. The window isn't clean. The breakfast is good enough, but not outstanding. We're paying a lot so there should be some thing that's excellent. The staff are polite and willing, but not happy. The wifi is terrible. In the evenings I often cannot even load a web page, or a sentence in Google translate. Or a picture in a news article. It's impossible to work or study. It's a low spot for our local Sim as well, so we can't even rely on that. We're not using a lot of data, web pages, zoom Mtgs and education apps. When I talked to the manager he made heaps of excuses. He tried to tell me the wifi situation was hard for them too... He talked about the situation in their country‚Ä¶ I feel he's not being honest. How can they run their business if they can't load a web page each evening? It might be Burma, but that's a bit too much to believe. We're staying for 2 weeks!
The only plus was the good and complimentary laundry service. (it should be complementary too! We're paying a lot and not getting much value for money). I since discover that was a special deal for us, it's not usually complimentary.
The only reason we returned here is the location is suitable for us. But there's other hotels nearby and we're going to try another one. I hope I don't have to stay here again.
I feel like the management, and therefore the staff, are not honest ) (The staff were lovely, friendly and helpful, but they have to do what the management says. They have to follow the rules.)
The hotel prefers you to pay in USD instead of local money (kyat), and they make the exchange rate heavily in their favour. When the kyat is down, it should be a cheaper USD price, but they never adjust. More dishonesty.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Thant Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Very attentive service and very well maintained facility. Rooms are well furnished and all necessary amenities are provided. Though not on the main street or downtown, the location is easy to access to airport, bus terminal and to the city center. Not for luxury but strongly recommended for business travelers and for those looking for short stay in Yangon, (or for transit). Breakfast is not very outstanding but it is quite good. Restaurant open for 24 hrs, and mostly limited choices for Asian Fusion. The lake and the small park for morning exercise or evening stroll is the plus.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Xes Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfdkB_bldIRglbJvxqdHGwIF4oAjCtZ0lG-1spNGhV2ycluoiIQtGESzww3Hy2yHj2f2w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I recommend this hotel if you have an early flight because it is close to the airport. We arrived in Yangon early in the morning after a 9 hour bus ride from Bagan. The receptionist greeted us and was able to check us in, in no time. She gave us orange juice as refreshments afterwards she hand us our room key and wifi password. Once we're settled in the room we immediately check if the wifi is working but both our phones aren't able to connect so we went down to the receptionist and have it checked. She eventually rebooted the router and that solved the problem so in case you encounter the same problem when you get there just ask the receptionist to turn the router on and off to save time since they don't have any IT guy around to fix it. They have quite a lot of options for breakfast especially if you're an early bird and the dining room is nice compared to other hotels we've stayed at it is very accessible too it's just located beside the reception area or if you don't want to get pass reception there's a door on the far right side of the elevator at the ground level if you just went down from your room. Our room is clean and have large windows with views of houses and buildings. This hotel is situated on the quiet side of Yangon beside a Buddhist Monastery that's why we had a real good sleep. There's a 24 hour lift and no power outages, thank God. There's no iron/ironing board available to rent but the receptionist offered someone to have my clothes ironed for free she asked some guy to come up to pick up and deliver my clothes which is okay though I'd prefer to do it myself if possible. I just noticed that Internet in Myanmar is not very fast so don't expect a lot when it comes to that. They arranged a taxi to take us to the airport the next day but it is not a free service offered by the hotel. They do not have airport pick up and drop off fyi. Overall, we had a nice and comfortable stay at this modern hotel it is far better than other hotels in the area.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rikkert O","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfnSFWXMd1oJu73a6IhdtgibYcjse2HKQTHeghNQd9Cyw8DYQQJZDCyh-TD68ehXuY-FA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Very modern style hotel with good rooms. ||We chose to stay here for a few hours, because our flight was leaving at 7AM. The staff was helpful and the rooms were clean and modern. ||We ordered some food, which was also okay. Nothing special! ||||Would advise this hotel for people flying out of town or taking the bus. However definitely not an hotel if you want to see Yangon itself!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Susie H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed at this hotel for 8 nights during my third trip to Yangon with a group of people. The hotel itself was very clean with functioning elevators. The breakfast buffet was not the best was modest but pretty decent. The location itself is not too close to Downtown Yangon - it was a 40 minute taxi ride for us. But it is located across the street from a decent sized super market (Orange Market) and there's a lot of street food to try at night in the area.||One negative was that some days, I did come back to my room at night to find a lizard crawling on the wall. There were a few days when I woke up to find worms on the bathroom floor, which were cleaned up during the day time.||One thing I would advise though, is not to leave cash in the room. I left $50 in cash by accident in a visible place inside an empty bag, and returned later that night to only find $40. The reason why I did not dock any points for this though is because I immediately let the management know, and the manager immediately called a meeting with all his employees to found out what happened. When he couldn't figure out who it was, he gave me $10 from his own pocket, which I refused, but he insisted. I commend the management of this hotel, and would recommend this hotel to those who aren't looking to spend $100+ a night in Yangon, but also not a dirty, mosquito infested room for $25 a night.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Arlene C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I used this as a transit hotel to catch the bus to the Golden Rock the next morning from an evening flight. It is about 10-15 min from both the airport and highway bus terminal for 3,000 kyats each. The room was clean and comfortable,  smelled like bleach when I walked in so I knew it was cleaned very well. The smell didn't bother me. I did see a baby cockroach though on the wall. The power seems to go out periodically for no longer than a minute  (but seems like much longer while it happens multiple times when you're showering). There is even a sign in the elevator stating that if the power goes out, to just wait one minute and the elevator will resume. Breakfast was average, fried rice, noodles, fried veggies, eggs and toast. The staff was probably the least assertive staff I had encountered in Myanmar but still kind nonetheless.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Minna R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Convenient hotel for both the highway bus stop and airport. Ten minutes to the airport, 15 to the bus terminal. Restaurant is nothing special, but they were very friendly to make breakfast for us at 6am even though it's not part of the schedule. Our room was clean and had a tub.","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: High Five Hotel

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Doreen W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qczn4VDfUM6-AtEt-6oaNazFa-i9Fy6kqPVfGIlPil6vJulEYyK8t930jZwOW4hD80mzw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This hotel suits our needs very well.
